race.comment: As far as provincial-grade 1800m maidens go, this is one of the better ones. GOLDEN GURU (8) started close to favourite in the Hill Smith Stakes last start and, while he didn't run up to market expectation, he wasn't disgraced. This is a much easier assignment and he looks the clear top seed. He maps well from a middle draw and will get his chance to break through. GOLDFIELDS GREY (2) was ridden to hold an on-speed position last start but the early work told later. He's better than that and with a quieter ride he might be able to win. YOUBEEFORTY (7) can run a cheeky race at a bigger price while PAGANINI (5) who put in a solid effort last start to finish third over 1500m at Gawler is a must include.
